<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-346-624  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 346 624.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  April 1990 v7 n4 p41(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Both media work together. (optical storage versus magneticWinchester servers) (Collisions)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dean, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Optical disk storage and magnetic Winchester technologies exist ascomplementary forms of mass storage for LAN file servers.andP;  Opticaldisk storage provides large capacity, direct access, andremovability.andP;  The 5.25-inch form-factor capacities are currentlyat 0.5Gbytes per side and are expected to increase.andP;  Write once,read many (WORM) optical disk storage on LANs provide automaticbackup and eliminate the need for a transaction log for LANfailure reconstruction purposes.andP;  The LAN library market waslimited by the lack of effective queuing algorithms, but thisproblem is being addressed by several manufacturers.andP;  Opticaltechnology is currently in its third generation; MagneticWinchester disk drives are eight generations into the program.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Optical MemoryOptical DisksWORMWinchester DiskLocal Area Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>